<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the products covered by Council Regulation (EEC) No 804/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in milk and milk products (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 559/76 (4), are at present substantially and increasingly in surplus; whereas it therefore seems justified to encourage the trend noted among certain groups of holdings in the Community to cease milk production, or the marketing of milk and milk products; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu 27. juuni 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 804/68 (piima- ja piimatooteturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 559/76 (4)) h&otilde;lmatud toodete turul on hetkel m&auml;rgatavad ning suurenevad &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;gid; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks soodustada &uuml;henduse teatavates talumajapidamiste r&uuml;hmades ilmnenud suundumust l&otilde;petada piimatootmine v&otilde;i piima ja piimatoodete turustamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this aim may be achieved by granting premiums to farmers who cease to market milk and milk products or who convert their dairy herds to meat production; whereas, however, in the case of a Member State where the increase of cattle numbers is difficult and consequently dairy herds have already been considerably reduced, it may prove advisable to authorize that Member State not to apply the provisions concerning the non-marketing and conversion premium; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse eesm&auml;rgi v&otilde;ib saavutada, andes lisatasu talupidajatele, kes l&otilde;petavad piima v&otilde;i piimatoodete turustamise v&otilde;i kes korraldavad oma l&uuml;psikarjad &uuml;mber lihatootmiseks; sellise liikmesriigi puhul, kus kariloomade arvu suurendamine on raske ning kus l&uuml;psikarju on seet&otilde;ttu juba oluliselt v&auml;hendatud, v&otilde;ib siiski olla soovitav lubada k&otilde;nealusel liikmesriigil mitte kohaldada turustamata j&auml;tmise ja &uuml;mberkorraldamise lisatasu k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the amount of the premiums should be fixed at a level such that they may be considered as some compensation for loss of income from the marketing of the products in question; whereas it therefore appears necessary to fix the amount of the premiums according to the quantity of products marketed in 1976; </inglise>
<eesti> lisatasude summa tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata nii, et seda v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitada teatava h&uuml;vitisena k&otilde;nealuste toodete turustamisest saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu eest; seet&otilde;ttu oleks soovitav lisatasude summa kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata 1976. aastal turustatud toodete koguse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the total amount of the premiums granted to a holding should be limited, so as to improve the structure of dairy farming on holdings that are economically more viable; whereas, however, provision should be made for certain exceptions to these limits where the applicant is taking part in a programme to eradicate brucellosis, tuberculosis and leucosis; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;hele talumajapidamisele antavate lisatasude kogusumma peaks olema piiratud, et parandada piimakarjakasvatuse struktuuri majanduslikult eluj&otilde;ulisemates talumajapidamistes; siiski tuleks s&auml;testada teatavad erandid k&otilde;nealustest piirm&auml;&auml;radest, kui taotleja osaleb brutselloosi, tuberkuloosi ja leukoosi h&auml;vitamise programmis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas to facilitate checks on compliance with the obligations arising from the application of this Regulation, the premiums should be paid in several instalments; </inglise>
<eesti> lisatasu tuleks maksta mitme osamaksena, et h&otilde;lbustada k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamisest tulenevate kohustuste t&auml;itmise kontrollimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these measures are designed on the one hand to restore the balance on the market in the products concerned and therefore may be regarded as intervention within the meaning of Article 3 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 729/70 of 21 April 1970 on the financing of the common agricultural policy (5), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2788/72 (6), and on the other to achieve the objectives set out in Article 39 (1) (a) of the Treaty, including the changes necessary for the proper working of the common market; whereas they therefore constitute common measures within the meaning of Article 6 of the said Regulation; Whereas the Community financing of the expenditure should therefore be provided by the Guidance and the Guarantee Sections of the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund, (1) OJ No C 93, 18.4.1977, p. 11. (2) OJ No C 77, 30.3.1977, p. 15. (3) OJ No L 148, 28.6.1968, p. 13. (4) OJ No L 67, 15.3.1976, p. 9. (5) OJ No L 94, 28.4.1970, p. 13. (6) OJ No L 295, 3.12.1972, p. 1. </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused meetmed on kavandatud &uuml;helt poolt tasakaalu taastamiseks k&otilde;nealuste toodete turul, mist&otilde;ttu neid meetmeid v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitleda sekkumisena n&otilde;ukogu 21. aprilli 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 729/70 (&uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika rahastamise kohta, (5) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2788/72 (6)) artikli 3 t&auml;henduses, ning teiselt poolt asutamislepingu artikli 39 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis a s&auml;testatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks, sealhulgas &uuml;histuru n&otilde;uetekohaseks toimimiseks vajalike muudatuste tegemiseks; seep&auml;rast on k&otilde;nealused meetmed &uuml;hismeetmed k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 6 t&auml;henduses; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks s&auml;testada, et Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi arendusrahastu ja tagatisrahastu kannavad &uuml;hendusepoolsed kulutused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to facilitate the administrative and financial management of the system of premiums, the dispositions laid down by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2697/70 of 29 December 1970, on the procedure for making Community funds available to Member States under the Guarantee Section of the EAGGF (1) and by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1723/72 of 26 July 1972 on making up accounts for the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund, Guarantee Section (2) should be applied, by way of exception, to the expenses financed by the Guidance Section; whereas, however, the normal system of reimbursement by the EAGGF, Guidance Section may, during a transitional period, be applied at the request of a Member State, </inglise>
